Why AGPL-3.0?

We chose the AGPL-3.0 deliberately. Unlike permissive licenses (MIT, Apache),
the AGPL ensures that:

  - Anyone can use, study, modify, and distribute PimPam.
  - Any modified version must also be released under the same license.
  - If someone runs a modified version as a web service, they must make
    their source code available to all users of that service.

This last point is critical. The "network use" clause (Section 13 of the AGPL)
closes the "SaaS loophole" that exists in the regular GPL. No corporation can
take PimPam's code, modify it behind closed doors, and run it as a proprietary
service. If they use our code, their users get the source.

The people's platform stays the people's platform. Always.

